<section id="camera-ready-submission" class="terms-of-service section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="tos-header">
            <span class="last-updated">RECCAP 2026</span>
            <h2>Camera Ready Submission</h2>
            <p>
                Instructions for the authors of IEEE International Conference on Recent Advances in
                Electronics, Communication, Computing, Automation and Power (RECCAP 2026) at IIT
                Palakkad, 22-24 May 2026.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="tos-content">
            <div class="content-section">
                <div class="alert alert-primary">
                    <h4>Official Camera Ready Submission PDF</h4>
                    <p>Open the official document shared by the conference team.</p>
                    <a href="{{cameraReadySubmissionPdf}}" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                        View PDF
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section">
                <p>
                    Before camera ready paper submission, the authors are required to go through the
                    IEEE paper submission policies available at this link:
                    <a href="https://conferences.ieeeauthorcenter.ieee.org/author-ethics/guidelines-and-policies/submission-policies/"
                        target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                        IEEE paper submission policies
                    </a>.
                </p>
                <p>Specific instructions regarding camera ready submission to RECCAP 2026 are as follows:</p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section">
                <h3>Step 1: Final Camera-ready paper preparation</h3>
                <p>
                    Authors have to complete the registration process before uploading the camera-ready
                    paper and e-copyright form as per the stipulated final dates.
                </p>
                <ol class="ps-3 mb-0">
                    <li>
                        Please follow the IEEE two-column A4 size standard conference format for preparing your
                        final manuscript. For more details, please visit the IEEE Templates page:
                        <a href="https://www.ieee.org/conferences/publishing/templates.html" target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener">IEEE Templates</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Revised Version: Revise your paper based on reviewers' comments/suggestions. Authors
                        are responsible for ensuring that the comments given by reviewers and meta-reviewers
                        are addressed in the final manuscript. The reviewer's comments are available on the
                        same Microsoft paper management site:
                        <a href="https://cmt3.research.microsoft.com/RECCAP2026" target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener">Reviewer Comments</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Use good-resolution images and diagrams. The resolution should not be too low or too
                        high. A resolution of 300 dpi is generally recommended. Do not paginate (don't insert
                        page numbers) your paper. Check for any further typos and grammatical errors, and
                        verify the tables and figures for correct captions. Ensure the quality of everything by
                        printing the paper and thoroughly cross-checking it against the IEEE standard template.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The maximum allowable pages in the camera-ready paper are 6 pages. A maximum of 2
                        additional pages is permitted at an extra page charge. The additional payment required
                        for extra pages is Rs.1000/page for Indian authors of all categories and USD 20/page
                        for all categories of foreign authors.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The camera-ready paper should exhibit low similarity with previously published
                        literature. Typically, a total similarity index below 30%, excluding references, is
                        acceptable, provided that the similarity with any individual source does not exceed 10%
                        and appropriate correct citations are given for the sources. Verbatim reproduction of
                        text, equations, tables, figures, or images from other sources is not permitted unless
                        properly quoted, cited, and used with the necessary permissions.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The manuscript must be submitted in PDF (.pdf) format with a maximum file size of 5
                        MB. The PDF file should not be encrypted or password-protected, and all fonts must
                        be embedded in the document.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section">
                <h3>Step 3: PDF eXpress check</h3>
                <p>
                    Before creating a PDF, proofread your source document thoroughly to confirm that it will
                    require no revision.
                </p>
                <h4>Creating your PDF eXpress Account</h4>
                <p>Log in to the IEEE PDF eXpress site:</p>
                <p>
                    <a href="https://ieee-pdf-express.org/account/login" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                        https://ieee-pdf-express.org/account/login
                    </a>
                </p>
                <p>First-time users should do the following:</p>
                <ol class="ps-3">
                    <li>Create Account</li>
                    <li>
                        Enter the following:
                        <ul class="ps-3 mb-0">
                            <li><strong>Conference ID:</strong> 69368X</li>
                            <li><strong>Email address:</strong> your email address</li>
                            <li><strong>Password:</strong> a password</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Continue to enter information as prompted.</li>
                </ol>
                <p>
                    An online confirmation will be displayed and an email confirmation will be sent verifying
                    your account setup.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Previous users of PDF eXpress need to follow the above steps but should enter the same
                    password that was used for previous conferences. Verify that your contact information is
                    valid.
                </p>
                <h4>Contacting PDF eXpress Support</h4>
                <p>
                    Access the IEEE Support Center for IEEE PDF eXpress:
                    <a href="https://supportcenter.ieee.org/app/answers/list/st/4/kw/PDF%2520eXpress/page/1/"
                        target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                        IEEE Support Center
                    </a>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    If you do not find an answer to your question on the IEEE Support Center, please email
                    <a href="mailto:PDFSupport@ieee.org">PDFSupport@ieee.org</a>.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section">
                <h3>Step 4: Renaming your PDF File for Submission</h3>
                <p>
                    The certified PDF file received from IEEE PDF eXpress will be assigned a filename in
                    the format <strong>0123456.pdf</strong>. Authors are required to rename this file
                    according to the following naming convention before uploading it to the submission
                    system.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>PIDXXX.pdf</strong>, where XXX is the paper ID of your paper in Microsoft CMT.
                    For example, if the CMT paper ID is 10, the file received from PDF eXpress should be
                    renamed to <strong>PID010.pdf</strong>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Authors are required to upload only those papers that have successfully passed the IEEE
                    PDF eXpress compliance check to the Microsoft CMT system, and only after completing
                    the conference registration in the appropriate category.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section">
                <h3>Step 5: Camera-ready Paper Submission</h3>
                <p>
                    After completing Step 4, submit the paper through the Author Console in Microsoft CMT.
                    Please note that the title of the paper must remain the same as in the originally
                    submitted version. Under no circumstances should the author list or the order of authors
                    be changed in the final manuscript.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-section">
                <h3>Step 6: Submission of the IEEE electronic copyright form</h3>
                <div class="alert alert-warning">
                    <strong>Important:</strong> Authors must ensure that all co-authors are registered in
                    Microsoft CMT using their correct names and contact email addresses. The IEEE
                    electronic copyright (e-copyright) system retrieves author information directly from CMT.
                    Any discrepancy between the author names in CMT and those listed in the manuscript may
                    result in the paper being excluded from the conference proceedings and not being uploaded
                    to IEEE Xplore.
                </div>
                <p>
                    Submission of the e-copyright form is a one-time process and cannot be modified once
                    completed. In case of any errors, authors must contact IEEE directly, as the conference
                    organizers are unable to make corrections.
                </p>
                <p>
                    After uploading the final camera-ready paper, which must have successfully passed the PDF
                    check in IEEE PDF eXpress, click on the <strong>Submit IEEE Copyright Form</strong>
                    link available in the Microsoft CMT Author Console. This will redirect you to the IEEE
                    Electronic Copyright Form (eCF) website to complete the copyright submission.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Once the IEEE Electronic Copyright Form and the required copyright agreements have been
                    completed, you will be able to download the finalized IEEE Copyright Form. The
                    corresponding author will also receive a copy of the completed form via email.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Please upload the downloaded copyright form to the same page in CMT using the upload
                    option (or the Drop files here area). The corresponding author may submit the copyright
                    form on behalf of all co-authors of the paper.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
